/259/okkara-kvinnur-foroyameistarar|title=Okkara kvinnur f\u00f8royameistarar|publisher=K\u00cd|date=20 September 2019}}</ref><br />''CC: 3.325''\n|{{fbaicon|NIR}} [[Linfield Ladies F.C.|Linfield]] {{small|(1st)}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/49834135|title=Women's Premiership: Linfield secure fourth straight title with 10-0 Derry win|publisher=BBC Sport|date=25 September 2019}}</ref><br />''CC: 1.660''\n|{{fbaicon|MNE}} {{small|(1st)}}\n|-\n|{{fbaicon|MLT}} {{small|(1st)}}\n|{{fbaicon|KOS}} {{small|(1st)}}\n|{{fbaicon|LVA}} [[FK Dinamo R\u012bga|Dinamo R\u012bga]] {{small|(1st)}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://lff.lv/zinas/12195/dinamo-riga-grauj-konkurentu-un-triumfe-latvijas-cempionata/|title=Dinamo R\u012bga grauj konkurentu un triumf\u0113 Latvijas \u010dempion\u0101t\u0101|publisher=Latvian Football Federation|date=29 September 2019}}</ref><br />''CC: 0.330''\n|{{fbaicon|MDA}} {{small|([[2019\u201320 Moldovan Women Top League|1st]])}}\n|-\n|{{fbaicon|MKD}} {{small|(1st)}}\n|{{fbaicon|GEO}} [[WFC Lanchkhuti|Lanchkhuti]] {{small|(1st)}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gff.ge/ge/media/news/19201|title=\u10da\u10d0\u10dc\u10e9\u10ee\u10e3\u10d7\u10d8 \u10e5\u10d0\u10da\u10d7\u10d0 \u10da\u10d8\u10d2\u10d8\u10e1 \u10d2\u10d0\u10db\u10d0\u10e0\u10ef\u10d5\u10d4\u10d1\u10e3\u10da\u10d8\u10d0|publisher=Georgian Football Federation|date=1 October 2019}}</ref><br />''CC: 0.000''\n|{{fbaicon|LUX}} {{small|(1st)}}\n|{{fbaicon|ARM}} {{small|(1st)}}\n|-\n|{{fbaicon|GIB}} [[Lincoln Red Imps F.C. (women)|Lincoln Red Imps]] {{small|(1st)}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://footballgibraltar.com/2020/02/robba-our-hard-work-throughout-the-season-has-once-again-paid-off/|title=Robba: \u201cOur hard work throughout the season has once again paid off\u201d|last=FootballGib|website=Football Gibraltar|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref><br />''CC: 0.000''\n|colspan=3|\n<!--\n|-\n|{{fbaicon|AND}} {{small|(1st)}}\n|{{fbaicon|AZE}} {{small|(1st)}}\n|{{fbaicon|LIE}} 