2003 World Netball Championships]] <ref name=\"2003todor66\">{{cite web|url=http://www.todor66.com/others/Netball/World/Women_2003.html|title=Women Netball XI World Championship 2003|publisher=www.todor66.com|accessdate=25 February 2020}}</ref>||4th\n|-\n|}\n\n==Coaching career==\n===Team Northumbria===\nNeville began her senior coaching career with [[Team Northumbria (netball)|Team Northumbria]] when she served as head coach for the [[2011 Netball Superleague season]]. <ref name=\"independent010415\">{{cite news | url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/general/others/tracey-neville-the-netball-coach-who-is-just-as-busy-as-her-brothers-gary-and-phil-10150224.html|title=Tracey Neville: The netball coach who is just as busy as her brothers, Gary and Phil|publisher=www.independent.co.uk|date=1 April 2015|accessdate=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"journal260111\">{{cite news | url=http://www.thejournal.co.uk/sport/other-sport/netball-tracey-neville-six-year-plan-4442119|title=Netball: Tracey Neville on a six-year plan|publisher=www.thejournal.co.uk|date=26 January 2011|accessdate=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"northernecho290111\">{{cite news| url=https://www.thenorthernecho.co.uk/news/8821079.nevilles-long-term-goal-team/|title=Neville's long-term goal for her team|publisher=www.thenorthernecho.co.uk|date=29 January 2011|accessdate=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"bbc121011\">{{cite web|title=Tracey Neville handed head job at Northern Thunder|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/netball/15272444|publisher=www.bbc.co.uk|accessdate=4 March 2020|date=12 October 2011}}</ref>\n\n===Manchester Thunder===\nBetween 2011 and 2015 Neville served as director of netball/head coach at [[Northern Thunder (netball)|Northern Thunder]]/[[Manchester Thunder]]. <ref name=\"bbc121011\">{{cite web|title=Tracey Neville handed head job at Northern Thunder|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/netball/15272444|publisher=www.bbc.co.uk|accessdate=4 March 2020|date=12 October 2011}}</ref><ref name=\"men121011\">{{cite web|url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/other-sport/netball-neville-takes-the-reins-as-boss-873013|title=Netball: Neville takes the reins as boss of Thunder|publisher=www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk|accessdate=18 March 2020|date=12 October 2011}}</ref><ref name=\"womensport151011\">{{cite web|url=http://www.womensportreport.com/netball-news-from-around-the/wn/14269|title=Netball News from around the globe|publisher=www.womensportreport.com|accessdate=3 March 2020|date=15 October 2011}}</ref><ref name=\"thunder190315\">{{cite web|url=https://www.manchesterthunder.co.uk/tracey-neville-named-as-interim-england-netball-head-coach/|title=Tracey Neville named as Interim England Netball Head Coach|publisher=www.manchesterthunder.co.uk|accessdate=7 March 2020|date=19 March 2015}}</ref> She guided Thunder to [[Netball Superleague]] titles in [[2012 Netball Superleague season|2012]] <ref name=\"bbc2012\">{{cite web|title=Manchester Thunder: Superleague winners in name change|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/netball/20169762|publisher=www.bbc.co.uk|accessdate=4 March 2020}}</ref> and [[2014 Netball Superleague season|2014]]. <ref name=\"bbc260414\">{{cite web|title=Netball Superleague: Manchester Thunder 49-48 Surrey Storm|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/netball/27176086|publisher=www.bbc.co.uk|accessdate=3 March 2020|date=26 April 2014}}</ref>\n\n===England===\nBetween 2015 and 2019 Neville served as head coach of [[England national netball team|England]]. <ref name=\"guardian190315\">{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2015/mar/19/neville-appointed-england-head-coach-for-world-cup|title=Neville appointed England head coach for World Cup (but it's Tracey not Gary)|publisher=www.theguardian.com|accessdate=19 March 2020|date=19 March 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"guardian030619\">{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2019/jun/03/tracey-neville-england-netball-step-down-world-cup|title=Tracey Neville to leave England role after Netball World Cup to start family|publisher=www.theguardian.com|date=3 June 2019}}</ref> She was initially appointed in March 2015 as an interim coach. <ref name=\"guardian190315\">{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2015/mar/19/neville-appointed-england-head-coach-for-world-cup|title=Neville appointed England head coach for World Cup (but it's Tracey not Gary)|publisher=www.theguardian.com|accessdate=19 March 2020|date=19 March 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"thunder190315\">{{cite web|url=https://www.manchesterthunder.co.uk/tracey-neville-named-as-interim-england-netball-head-coach/|title=Tracey Neville named as Interim England Netball Head Coach|publisher=www.manchesterthunder.co.uk|accessdate=7 March 2020|date=19 March 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"skysports270315\">{{cite news|title=England Netball have replaced head coach Anna Mayes with Tracey Neville|url=https://www.skysports.com/netball/news/12415/9766532/england-netball-have-replaced-head-coach-anna-mayes-with-tracey-neville|publisher=www.skysports.com|date=27 March 2015|accessdate=29 January 2018}}</ref> However after guiding England to the bronze medal at the [[2015 Netball World Cup]], the appointment was made permanent in September 2015. <ref name=\"bbc170915\">{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/netball/34281717|title=Tracey Neville given permanent England netball head coach role|publisher=www.bbc.com|accessdate=15 March 2020|date=17 September 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"skysports170915\">{{cite news|title=Tracey Neville appointed England netball coach on permanent basis|url=http://www.skysports.com/netball/news/12415/9994124/tracey-neville-appointed-england-netball-coach-on-permanent-basis|publisher=www.skysports.com|date=17 September 2015|accessdate=29 January 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"thunder170915\">{{cite web|url=https://www.manchesterthunder.co.uk/tracey-neville-confirmed-as-permanent-england-head-coach/|title=Tracey Neville confirmed as permanent England Head Coach|publisher=www.manchesterthunder.co.uk|accessdate=18 March 2020|date=17 September 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"men170915\">{{cite web|url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/gallery/tracey-neville-new-england-netball-8875312|title=Tracey Neville new England netball coach|publisher=www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk|accessdate=19 March 2020|date=17 September 2015}}</ref> On the eve of the World Cup tournament, Neville's father, [[Neville Neville]], died in a [[Sydney]] hospital. He and her brothers, [[Phil Neville|Phil]] and [[Gary Neville|Gary]] where all in [[Australia]] to support their daughter and sister. <ref name=\"bbc070815a\">{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-manchester-33816707|title=Neville Neville dies in Australia|publisher=www.bbc.com|accessdate=21 March 2020|date=7 August 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"mirror080815\">{{cite news|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/news/gary-phil-nevilles-sister-tracey-6218516|title=Gary and Phil Neville's sister Tracey leads England netball team to victory hours after father passes away|publisher=www.mirror.co.uk|accessdate=18 March 2020|date=8 August 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"bbc170915\">{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/netball/34281717|title=Tracey Neville given permanent England netball head coach role|publisher=www.bbc.com|accessdate=15 March 2020|date=17 September 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"bbc070815b\">{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/netball/33816812|title=Tracey Neville to stay with England squad after father's death|publisher=www.bbc.com|accessdate=21 March 2020|date=7 August 2015}}</ref> In [[2016 New Year Honours|2016]] Neville was awarded an {{post-nominals|country=GBR|MBE}}. <ref name=\"burytimes120716\">{{cite news|url=https://www.burytimes.co.uk/news/14613686.bury-netball-star-tracey-neville-honoured-with-mbe/|title=Bury netball star Tracey Neville honoured with MBE|publisher=www.burytimes.co.uk|accessdate=19 March 2020|date=12 July 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"skysports311215\">{{cite news|title=Tracey Neville heads list of sportswomen honoured in New Year list|url=https://www.skysports.com/more-sports/news/12040/10114808/tracey-neville-heads-list-of-sportswomen-honoured-in-new-year-list|publisher=www.skysports.com|date=31 December 2015|accessdate=21 March 2020}}</ref> \n\nNeville guided England to the 2015, 2016 and [[2017 European Netball Championship]]s. <ref name=\"bbc170515\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/netball/32772934|title=Netball Europe: England beat Northern Ireland to win title|publisher=www.bbc.co.uk|accessdate=20 March 2020|date=17 May 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"englandnetball160516\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.englandnetball.co.uk/roses-take-netball-europe-title/|title=Roses take Netball Europe title!|publisher=www.englandnetball.co.uk|accessdate=20 March 2020|date=16 May 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"bbc071017\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/netball/41540461|title=Europe Open Championships: England thrash Fiji 94-31 to maintain 100% record|publisher=www.bbc.co.uk|accessdate=20 March 2020|date=7 October 2017}}</ref> She was also head coach when England won the gold medal at the [[Netball at the 2018 Commonwealth Games|2018 Commonwealth Games]]. <ref name=\"men150418\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/news/greater-manchester-news/england-netball-coach-tracey-neville-14534279|title=England netball coach Tracey Neville hails 'dream come true' Commonwealth gold|publisher=www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk|accessdate=19 March 2020|date=15 April 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"bbc150418\">{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/commonwealth-games/43773102|title=Commonwealth Games: England shock Australia to win netball gold|publisher=www.bbc.com|accessdate=21 April 2018|date=15 April 2018 }}</ref><ref name=\"2018todor66\">{{cite web|url=http://www.todor66.com/others/Netball/Commonwealth/Women_2018.html|title=Women Netball Commonwealth Games Golden Goast, Australia 2018|publisher=www.todor66.com|accessdate=5 January 2020}}</ref> Neville later revealed that she suffered a [[miscarriage]] a day after leading England to netball Commonwealth gold. <ref name=\"bbc240919\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/netball/49751520|title=Netball: Tracey Neville had a miscarriage day after England Commonwealth gold|date=24 September 2019|publisher=www.bbc.co.uk}}</ref><ref name=\"bbc250919\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/netball/49751520|title=Tracey Neville: Natalie Haythornthwaite calls ex-England netball head coach 'incredible'|publisher=www.bbc.co.uk|accessdate=15 March 2020|date=25 September 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 2019 Neville and her twin brother, Phil, both coached England women's national teams to the semi-final stages in the [[2019 Netball World Cup]] and [[2019 FIFA Women's World Cup]] respectively. Phil coached the [[England women's national football team]]. <ref name=\"bbc010519\">{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/48010734|title=Phil & Tracey Neville on World Cups, family pride, legacies & big brother Gary|publisher=www.bbc.com|accessdate=18 March 2020|date=1 May 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"mirror060320\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/news/phil-nevilles-lionesses-making-sister-17248147|title=Phil Neville's Lionesses making his sister and fellow England boss Tracey roar|publisher=www.mirror.co.uk|accessdate=19 March 2020|date=25 June 2019}}</ref> After coaching England to a bronze medal at the 2019 Netball World Cup, Neville retired as head coach to start family. <ref name=\"guardian030619\">{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2019/jun/03/tracey-neville-england-netball-step-down-world-cup|title=Tracey Neville to leave England role after Netball World Cup to start family|publisher=www.theguardian.com|date=3 June 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"englandnetball210719\">{{cite web|url=https://www.englandnetball.co.uk/vitality-roses-pay-tribute-outgoing-coach-tracey-neville/|title=Vitality Roses pay tribute to outgoing coach Tracey Neville|p