r66.com/others/Netball/Commonwealth/Women_2018.html|title=Women Netball Commonwealth Games Golden Goast, Australia 2018|publisher=www.todor66.com|accessdate=5 January 2020}}</ref> ||{{gold01}}\n|-\n|[[2018 Netball Quad Series (September)]] <ref name=\"englandnetball230918\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.englandnetball.co.uk/incredible-comeback-secures-final-quad-series-win-roses/|title=Incredible comeback secures final Quad Series win for the Roses|publisher=www.englandnetball.co.uk|accessdate=20 March 2020|date=23 September 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"teamengland260918\">{{Cite web|url=https://teamengland.org/news/england-roses-equal-best-ever-quad-series-finish|title=England Roses equal best ever Quad Series finish|publisher=teamengland.org|accessdate=20 March 2020|date=26 September 2018}}</ref>||2nd\n|-\n|[[2019 Netball Quad Series]] <ref name=\"guardian200119\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2019/jan/20/rachel-dunn-england-australia-quad-series-tracey-neville|title=Rachel Dunn guides England to victory but Australia claim Quad Series|publisher=www.theguardian.com|accessdate=20 March 2020|date=20 January 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"bbc200119\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/netball/46941187|title=England beat Australia 52-49 but miss out on Quad Series|publisher=www.bbc.co.uk|accessdate=20 March 2020|date=20 January 2019}}</ref>||2nd\n|-\n|[[2019 Netball World Cup]] <ref name=\"guardian030619\">{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2019/jun/03/tracey-neville-england-netball-step-down-world-cup|title=Tracey Neville to leave England role after Netball World Cup to start family|publisher=www.theguardian.com|date=3 June 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"englandnetball210719\">{{cite web|url=https://www.englandnetball.co.uk/vitality-roses-pay-tribute-outgoing-coach-tracey-neville/|title=Vitality Roses pay tribute to outgoing coach Tracey Neville|publisher=www.englandnetball.co.uk|accessdate=18 March 2020|date=21 July 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"bbc230519\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/netball/48337417|title=Netball World Cup 2019: Tracey Neville names England Roses squad|publisher=www.bbc.co.uk|accessdate=27 February 2020|date=23 May 2019}}</ref>||{{bronze03}}\n|-\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n===Player===\n;[[Northern Thunder (netball)|Northern Thunder]]\n*'''[[AENA Super Cup|Super Cup]]'''\n**''Winners'': 2002: '''1'''\n===Coach===\n;[[England national netball team|England]]\n*'''[[Netball at the Commonwealth Games|Commonwealth Games]]'''\n**''Winners'': [[Netball at the 2018 Commonwealth Games|2018]]: '''1'''\n*'''[[European Netball Championship]]'''\n**''Winners'': 2015, 2016, [[2017 European Netball Championship|2017]] '''3'''\n*'''[[Netball Quad Series]]'''\n**''Runners Up'': [[2018 Netball Quad Series (January)|2018 (Jan)]], [[2018 Netball Quad Series (September)|2018 (Sep)]], [[2019 Netball Quad Series|2019]] '''3'''\n;[[Northern Thunder (netball)|Northern Thunder]]/[[Manchester Thunder]]\n*'''[[Netball Superleague]]'''\n**''Winners'': [[2012 Netball Superleague season|2012]], [[2014 Netball Superleague season|2014]]: '''2'''\n*'''[[Mike Greenwood Trophy]]'''\n**''Winners'': 2012, 2013, 2014\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|3}}\n\n{{Navboxes\n|title=England squads\n|bg=red\n|fg=white\n|list1=\n{{England netball squad at the 2015 World Netball Cup}}\n{{2018 Commonwealth Games England netball team squad}}\n{{England netball squad at the 2019 World Netball Cup}}\n}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Neville, Tracey}}\n[[Category:1977 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:English netball players]]\n[[Category:English netball coaches]]\n[[Category:England national netball team coaches]]\n[[Category:Netball players at the 1998 Commonwealth Games]]\n[[Category:Netball players at the 2002 Commonwealth Games]]\n[[Category:Commonwealth Games bronze medallists for England]]\n[[Category:Commonwealth Games medallists in netball]]\n[[Category:Manchester Thunder players]]\n[[Category:Leeds Carnegie/Yorkshire Jets players]]\n[