{"title_page": "British America", "text_new": "{{short description|Former British territories in North America}}\n\n{{For|American people of British descent|British Americans}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2014}}\n{{Use American English|date = November 2019}}\n{{Infobox former country\n|native_name=\n|conventional_long_name = British America and<br />the British West Indies\n|common_name=British America\n|region    =\n|status    = Colonies\n|status_text= Colonies of England <small>(1607\u20131707)</small><br />Colonies of Great Britain <small>(1707\u20131783)</small>\n|empire    = Britain\n|life_span = 1607\u20131783\n|government_type    = Constitutional monarchy\n|event_start = [[Colony of Virginia]]\n|year_start  = 1607\n|date_start  =\n|event_end   = [[Treaty of Paris (1783)|Treaty of Paris]]\n|year_end    = 1783\n|date_end    =\n|event1      = Bermuda\n|date_event1 = 1614\n|event2      = [[Plymouth Council for New England]] ([[Massachusetts Bay Colony]])\n|date_event2 = 1620\n|event3      = [[Province of Maryland]]\n|date_event3 = 1634\n|event4      = Jamaica\n|date_event4 = 1655\n|event5      = [[Rupert's Land]]\n|date_event5 = 1670\n|event6      = [[Treaty of Utrecht (1713)|Treaty of Utrecht]]\n|date_event6 = 1713\n|event7      = [[Treaty of Paris (1763)|Treaty of Paris]] ([[French and Indian War]])\n|date_event7 = 1763\n|event8      = [[American Revolutionary War]]\n|date_event8 = 1775\u20131783\n|event9      = \n|date_event9 = \n|p1          = New Netherland\n|flag_p1     = Prinsenvlag.svg\n|p2          = New France\n|flag_p2     = Royal Standard of King Louis XIV.svg\n|p3          = Spanish Florida\n|flag_p3     = Flag of New Spain.svg\n|p4          = New Sweden\n|flag_p4     = Sweden-Flag-1562.svg\n|s1          = British North America\n|flag_s1     = Flag of Great Britain (1707-1800).svg\n|s2          = British West Indies\n|flag_s2     = Flag of Great Britain (1707-1800).svg\n|s3          = United States\n|flag_s3     = US flag 13 stars \u2013 Betsy Ross.svg\n|s4          = Spanish Florida\n|flag_s4     = Flag of New Spain.svg\n|flag_type   = [[Red Ensign#Flag of British America|Flag of British America]] (after 1707)\n|image_flag  = Colonial-Red-Ensign.svg\n|symbol                 =\n|symbol_type            =\n|image_coat             =\n|image_map    = British America.png\n|image_map_caption  = British colonies in America (red) and the island colonies of the British West Indies near the Caribbean Sea (pink)\n|capital          = Administered from London, England\n|national_motto   =\n|national_anthem  =\n|common_languages = English (official) <br /> Spoken languages: <br /> English <br /> German <br /> French <br /> Spanish <br /> Dutch <br /> Irish <br /> Scottish Gaelic <br /> [[Ojibwe language|Ojibwe]] <br /> Indian languages\n|religion         = Anglicanism, Protestantism, Lutheranism, Roman Catholicism, Judaism, American Indian religion\n|currency         = Pound sterling, Spanish dollar, colonial money, bills of credit, commodity money, and many local currencies\n||<!--- Titles and names of the first and last leaders and their deputies --->\n|leader1      = [[James I of England|James I and VI]] <small>(first)</small>\n|year_leader1 = 1607\u20131625\n|leader2      = [[George III of the United Kingdom|George III]] <small>(last)</small>\n|year_leader2 = 1760\u20131783\n|title_leader = Monarch\n||legislature  =\n||<!--- Area and population of a given year --->\n|stat_year1 =\n|stat_area1 =\n|stat_pop1  =\n|stat_year2 =\n|stat_pop2  =\n|political_subdiv =\n|today = {{Collapsible list|title=Countries today|\n{{flag|Anguilla}}|{{flag|Antigua and Barbuda}}|{{flag|Bahamas}}|{{flag|Barbados}}|{{flag|Belize}}|{{flag|Bermuda}}|{{flag|British Virgin Islands}}|{{flag|Canada}}|{{flag|Cayman Islands}}|{{flag|Dominica}}|{{flag|Grenada}}|{{flag|Guyana}}|{{flag|Honduras}}|{{flag|Jamaica}}|{{flag|Montserrat}}|{{flag|Nicaragua}}|{{flag|Saint Kitts and Nevis}}|{{flag|Saint Vincent and the Grenadines}}|{{flag|Trinidad and Tobago}}|{{flag|Turks and Caicos Islands|name=Turks and Caicos}}|{{flag|United States}}\n}}\n|footnotes  =\n}}\n\n'''British America''' refers to the [[British Empire]]'s colonial territories in America from 1607 to 1783. These colonies were formally known as '''British America''' and the '''British West Indies''' before the [[Thirteen Colonies]] fought for their independence in the [[American Revolutionary War]] (1775\u20131783) and formed the United States of America.<ref>{{cite web|title=A Summary View of the Rights of British America \u2013 Thomas Jefferson|url=http://press-pubs.uchicago.edu/founders/documents/v1ch14s10.html}}</ref> After the [[American Revolution]], the term [[British North America]] referred to the remainder of Great Britain's Canadian possessions. That term was first used informally in 1783, but it was uncommon before the ''Report on the Affairs of British North America'' (1839), generally known as the ''[[Durham Report]]''.\n\nBritish America gained large amounts of territory with the [[Treaty of Paris (1763)]], which ended the [[French and Indian War]] in America and the [[Seven Years' War]] in Europe. At the start of the Revolutionary War in 1775, the British Empire included 23 colonies and territories on the North American continent. The [[Treaty of Paris (1783)]] ended the war, and Britain lost much of this territory to the newly formed United States. In addition, Britain ceded [[East Florida|East]] and [[West Florida]] to the Kingdom of Spain, which in turn ceded them to the United States in 1821. Most of the remaining colonies to the north formed Canada in 1867, with the [[Dominion of Newfoundland]] joining in 1949.\n\n== History ==\n{{Main|English overseas possessions#The Americas}}\n{{further|First British Empire}}\n[[File:Senex, Price, and Maxwell North America 1710 UTA.jpg|thumb|British map of North America, 1710]]\n\nA number of English colonies were established in America between 1606 and 1670 by individuals and companies whose investors expected to reap rewards from their speculation. They were granted commercial charters by [[James VI and I|King James I]], [[Charles I of England|King Charles I]], Parliament, and [[Charles II of England|King Charles II]]. The [[London Company]] founded the first permanent settlement in 1607 on the [[James River (Virginia)|James River]] at [[Jamestown, Virginia]] upstream from [[Chesapeake Bay]]. This was followed in 1620 when the Pilgrims established the [[Plymouth settlement]] in [[New England]]. English Catholics settled the [[Province of Maryland]] in 1634, with [[Cecil Calvert, 2nd Baron Baltimore|Cecilus Calvert, second Lord Baltimore]].\n\nA state department in London known as the [[Southern Department (United Kingdom)|Southern Department]] governed all the colonies beginning in 1660, as well as a committee of the [[Privy Council of England|Privy Council]] called the [[Board of Trade and Plantations]]. In 1768, Parliament created a specific [[Colonial Office#First Colonial Office (1768\u20131782)|state department]] for America, but it was disbanded in 1782 when the [[Home Office]] took responsibility for the remaining possessions of [[British North America]] in eastern Canada, the Floridas, and the West Indies.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.thecanadianencyclopedia.com/en/article/colonial-office/ |title=Colonial Office |last=Foulds |first=Nancy Brown |website=The Canadian Encyclopedia |language=en |access-date=2018-07-07}}</ref>\n\n== North American colonies in 1775 ==\n\nThe [[Thirteen Colonies]] that became the original states of the United States:\n\n:; [[New England Colonies]]:\n:*[[Province of Massachusetts Bay]]\n:*[[Province of New Hampshire]]\n:*[[Colony of Rhode Island and Providence Plantations]]<ref name=\"King Charles II Rhode Island Charter\" /><ref name=\"Church History \u2013 King Charles II Rhode Island Charter\" />\n:*[[Connecticut Colony]]\n\n[[File:A view of Fort George with the city of New York, from the SW.jpg|thumb|A view of [[Fort Amsterdam|Fort George]] and the city of [[New York City|New York]] c. 1731]]\n:; [[Middle Colonies]]:\n:*[[Province of New York]]\n:*[[Province of New Jersey]]\n:*[[Province of Pennsylvania]]\n:*[[Delaware Colony]]\n\n:; [[Southern Colonies]]:\n:*[[Province of Maryland]]\n:*[[Colony of Virginia]]\n:*[[Province of North Carolina]]\n:*[[Province of South Carolina]]\n:*[[Province of Georgia]]\n\nColonies and territories that became part of Canada:\n\n:*[[Province of Quebec (1763\u20131791)|Province of Quebec]] northeast of the [[Great Lakes]] (including [[Labrador]] until 1791)\n:*[[Nova Scotia]] (including [[New Brunswick]] until 1784)\n:*[[Prince Edward Island|Island of St. John]]\n:*[[Colony of Newfoundland]]\n:*[[Rupert's Land]]\n:*[[North-Western Territory]]\n:*[[British Arctic Territories]]\n\nColonies and territories that were ceded to Spain or the United States in 1783:\n\n:*Province of [[East Florida]] (Spanish 1783\u20131823, U.S. after 1823)\n:*Province of [[West Florida]] (Spanish 1783-1823, U.S. after 1823)\n:*[[Indian Reserve (1763)|Indian Reserve]] (U.S. after 1783)\n:*[[Province of Quebec (1763\u20131791)|Province of Quebec]] southwest of the [[Great Lakes]] (U.S. after 1783)\n\n== Colonies in the Caribbean, Mid-Atlantic, and South America in 1783 ==\n:*[[Bermuda]]\n:; Divisions of the [[British Leeward Islands]]:\n:*[[Saint Kitts|Saint Christopher]] (de facto capital)\n:*[[Antigua]]\n:*[[Barbuda]]\n:*[[British Virgin Islands]]\n:*[[Montserrat]]\n:*[[Nevis]]\n:*[[Anguilla]]\n\n:; [[British West Indies, Jamaica and dependencies|Island of Jamaica and its dependencies]]:\n:*Island of [[Jamaica]]\n:*Settlement of Belize in [[British Honduras]]\n:*[[Mosquito Coast]]\n:*[[Bay Islands (department)|Bay Islands]]\n:*[[Cayman Islands]]\n\n:; Other possessions in the [[British Windward Islands]]:\n:*Island of [[Barbados]]\n:*Island of [[Grenada]]\n:*[[Saint Vincent and the Grenadines|Island of St. Vincent]]\n:*Island of [[Tobago]] (detached from Grenada in 1768)\n:*Island of [[Dominica]] (detached from Grenada in 1770)\n\n== See also ==\n{{Portal|British Empire|History|Canada|North America|United States|Caribbean}}\n* [[British colonization of the Americas]]\n* [[British North America Acts]]\n* [[British overseas territories]]\n* [[Colonial history of the United States]]\n* [[Evolution of the British Empire]]\n* [[Former colonies and territories in Canada]]\n\n== Citations ==\n{{Reflist\n| refs =\n<ref name=\"King Charles II Rhode Island Charter\">{{cite web\n| url         = http://sos.ri.gov/library/history/charter/\n| title       = Rhode Island Royal Charter of 1663\n| author      =\n| date        =\n| month       =\n| year        =\n| work        = sos.ri.gov\n| publisher   = [[Secretary of State of Rhode Island]]\n| format      =\n| archiveurl  =\n| archivedate =\n| accessdate  = 14 April 2011\n| quote       =\n| postscript  = .\n}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Church History \u2013 King Charles II Rhode Island Charter\">{{cite web\n| url         = http://www.christianity.com/ChurchHistory/11630142/\n| title       = Charles II Granted Rhode Island New Charter\n| author      =\n| date        = 8 July 1663\n| month       =\n| year        =\n| work        = christianity.com\n| publisher   = [[Christianity.com]]\n| format      =\n| archiveurl  =\n| archivedate =\n| accessdate  = 14 April 2011\n| quote       =\n| postscript  = .\n}}</ref>\n\n<!-- the two entries below do nothing: is it necessary to define \"British\" as the UK did not formally come into being until the Act of Union 1707? See also Union_of_the_Crowns#British -->\nhttp://dictionary.reference.com/browse/British\nhttp://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/british\n}}\n\n{{coord missing|North America}}\n\n[[Category:1607 establishments in the British Empire]]\n[[Category:1783 disestablishments in North America]]\n[[Category:1783 disestablishments in the British Empire]]\n[[Category:British colonization of the Americas]]\n[[Category:British North America]]\n[[Category:Colonial United States (British)]]\n[[Category:Colonization history of the United States]]\n[[Category:English-speaking countries and territories]]\n[[Category:History of the Caribbean]]\n[[Category:States and territories established in 1607]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Former British territories in North America}}\n\n{{For|American people of British descent|British Americans}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2014}}\n{{Use American English|date = November 2019}}\n{{Infobox former country\n|native_name=\n|conventional_long_name = British America and<br />the British West Indies\n|common_name=British America\n|region    =\n|status    = Colonies\n|status_text= Colonies of England <small>(1607\u20131707)</small><br />Colonies of Great Britain <small>(1707\u20131783)</small>\n|empire    = Britain\n|life_span = 1607\u20131783\n|government_type    = Constitutional monarchy\n|event_start = [[Colony of Virginia]]\n|year_start  = 1607\n|date_start  =\n|event_end   = [[Treaty of Paris (1783)|Treaty of Paris]]\n|year_end    = 1783\n|date_end    =\n|event1      = Bermuda\n|date_event1 = 1614\n|event2      = [[Plymouth Council for New England]] ([[Massachusetts Bay Colony]])\n|date_event2 = 1620\n|event3      = [[Province of Maryland]]\n|date_event3 = 1634\n|event4      = Jamaica\n|date_event4 = 1655\n|event5      = [[Rupert's Land]]\n|date_event5 = 1670\n|event6      = [[Treaty of Utrecht (1713)|Treaty of Utrecht]]\n|date_event6 = 1713\n|event7      = [[Treaty of Paris (1763)|Treaty of Paris]] ([[French and Indian War]])\n|date_event7 = 1763\n|event8      = [[American Revolutionary War]]\n|date_event8 = 1775\u20131783\n|event9      = \n|date_event9 = \n|p1          = New Netherland\n|flag_p1     = Prinsenvlag.svg\n|p2          = New France\n|flag_p2     = Royal Standard of King Louis XIV.svg\n|p3          = Spanish Florida\n|flag_p3     = Flag of New Spain.svg\n|p4          = New Sweden\n|flag_p4     = Sweden-Flag-1562.svg\n|s1          = British North America\n|flag_s1     = Flag o